HEADWORD: Niccolite
<hw>Nic"co*lite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[from NL.
<ets>niccolum</ets> nickel.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A mineral of a
copper-red color and metallic luster; an arsenide of nickel; -- called
also <altname>coppernickel</altname>,
<altname>kupfernickel</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

